When you set `dummy.next` to `head`, `dummy` is now the beginning of the list. So you should set `head = dummy`. Such as:

```
class Solution {
    public ListNode rotateRight(ListNode head, int k) {
        if (head == null || head.next == null){
            return head;
        }
        for(int i=0;i&lt;k;i++){
            ListNode temp=head;
            ListNode last=head;
            
            while(temp.next!=null){
                if(temp.next.next==null) last=temp;
                temp=temp.next;
            }
            
             ListNode dummy=new ListNode(temp.val);
             dummy.next=head;
             last.next=null;
             head = dummy;
     
        }
        return head;
                
    }
}
```

