answers.body_markdown:
What happens with an iterator is that its usage looks like:

```
while (iterator.hasNext()) {
  doSomething(iterator.next());
}
```

and as it stands, `hasNext()` returns false _before_ `next()` has the chance to look for it.

Your `hasNext()` method will need to do all the work of finding the next entry, if there is one.

